Subject: Application for Engineering Manager Position - Bringing PayPal-Scale Experimentation Platform Leadership to RevenueCat

Dear RevenueCat Hiring Team,

I'm writing to express my enthusiastic interest in the Engineering Manager position at RevenueCat. When I discovered your role, I was immediately drawn to how closely my experience building PayPal's experimentation platform aligns with RevenueCat's mission of helping developers understand and grow their revenue.

As an Engineering Manager at PayPal, I lead a cross-functional team building experimentation platforms and AI-powered sales prospecting tools used by product teams globally to make revenue-critical decisions. Our platform processes thousands of experiments monthly, directly impacting multi-billion dollar decisions across PayPal's global operations—giving me firsthand insight into exactly the kind of developer tools that help teams optimize their revenue strategies.

My background combines deep technical expertise with proven leadership capabilities:

**Revenue-Focused Product Leadership**: At PayPal, I've built and scaled teams that create tools developers love—tools that transform complex data into actionable insights. This directly parallels RevenueCat's mission of removing subscription headaches and empowering developers with clear revenue understanding.

**Technical Depth with Hands-On Approach**: Before becoming an Engineering Manager, I served as Senior Staff Engineer, where I architected cloud-native platforms and established technical standards. This dual perspective allows me to provide meaningful technical guidance while maintaining strategic focus on team growth and product delivery.

**Cross-Functional Excellence**: I have extensive experience collaborating with product, design, and support teams to build prioritized roadmaps and deliver features that solve real customer problems. My team's work in improving PayPal's experimentation platform user experience demonstrates my commitment to building web-based tools with great UX.

**Data-Driven Leadership**: While my primary data work has been with big data systems at PayPal scale, I'm comfortable with SQL queries and regularly collaborate with data teams to extract insights, analyze inconsistencies, and make data-driven decisions that impact product direction.

What particularly excites me about RevenueCat is your customer-obsessed culture and focus on helping developers succeed. Having worked at PayPal's scale, I understand the challenges developers face in understanding and growing their revenue—and I'm passionate about building tools that make this process seamless and insightful.

**Location Flexibility**: I wanted to mention that I have a European passport and am fully prepared to relocate to Spain if needed. This means no visa sponsorship would be required, and I'm excited about the possibility of joining RevenueCat's European presence while contributing to your global remote-first culture.

I'm confident that my experience leading experimentation platform development, combined with my technical depth and leadership approach, would enable me to help RevenueCat continue to innovate and scale your monetization platform for developers worldwide.

I would welcome the opportunity to discuss how my background and passion for building developer-focused tools can contribute to RevenueCat's mission. Thank you for your consideration, and I look forward to the possibility of joining your team.

